<PartIntro Id="SDL-RESERVED-hometopic">
<Title>Mailer Help</Title>
<TitleAbbrev>Mailer Help</TitleAbbrev>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary SortAs="mailer, using">Mailer, using</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary SortAs="using mailer">using Mailer</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>introduction</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<Para>Use Mailer to send, receive, and manage your electronic mail messages.
When you receive an electronic message (email), you can:
</Para>
<ItemizedList Mark="&bull;" Role="tight">
<ListItem Id="HMLR.HTOP.item.1">
<Para>Save a message to a Mailbox in your file system
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.HTOP.item.2">
<Para>Reply to the sender of the message
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.HTOP.item.3">
<Para>Forward the message to another recipient along with your own message
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.HTOP.item.4">
<Para>Delete the message
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.HTOP.item.5">
<Para>Print the message
</Para>
</ListItem>
</ItemizedList>
<Para>You can send and receive attachments: image files, document files, or
executable files.</Para>
<Para>You can also drag and drop files from other desktop applications, such as
File Manager, for use as attachments in your mail messages.</Para>
<Procedure>
<Title>To Open Mailer</Title>
<Step>
<Para>Click the Mailer control in the Front Panel.</Para>
<Para>&newline;&empty;&newline;</Para>
<Graphic Entityref="mail-icon" Id="HMLR.HTOP.fig.1"></Graphic>
<!-- <p gentity=mail-icon> -->
<Para>&newline;&empty;</Para>
<Para>The mailbox appears, displaying message headers and a view of the
selected message.</Para>
<Para>&newline;&empty;
</Para>
<Para><InlineGraphic Remap="graphic" Role="left" Entityref="MMailBox"></InlineGraphic>&newline;&empty;</Para>
</Step>
</Procedure>
